   https://www.sublimetext.com/blog/articles/sublime-text-3-point-1 Mon, 7
   May 2018 10:00:00 +0000 Will Bond and Jon Skinner <p>Since version 3.0
   we've been shipping frequent <a href="/3dev">dev builds</a>, refining
   Sublime Text for a more polished experience all-around. Those dev
   builds are now rolling out to everyone as Sublime Text 3.1. The <a
   href="/3">full changelog for 3.1</a> includes every detail, but the
   following are some we'd like to highlight: </p> <style> img.screenshot
   { width: 600px; margin: 1em 0 0; display: block; filter:
   drop-shadow(3px 3px 5px #9998); } p.caption { margin-top: 0.5em; color:
   #999; font-style: italic; } </style> <h4>UI</h4> <ul class="topic">
   <li>Windows 10/8.1 per-monitor DPI settings for handling mixed monitor
