   Mon, 05 Nov 2018 02:00:00 -0500 Will Bond <p> While we continue to add
   more features and polish to the default Sublime Merge experience, we
   know that developers love the ability to tweak their tools. Sublime
   Merge is built on the same foundation as Sublime Text, so you can tweak
   key bindings, menus, command palette entries, and even the look and
   feel of the UI. </p> <p> To assist, we™ve just rolled out a number of <a
   href="https://www.sublimemerge.com/docs/">pages of documentation</a>
   for users who wish to customize Sublime Merge to look and function a
   little differently. In addition, we™ve added a <a
